Meet <b>Thoedog</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Thoedog lives at <a href='/home/?user=theodog'>1959 Arrowhead Avenue</a>, in the breezy, scenic neighborhood of Lakeview.  He has been a citizen of Millsberry since August 29th of 2004, and has enjoyed being in the community as much as we have enjoyed having him here!<br><br>Besides possessing an easy-going personality,  Thoedog is also very good at sports.  His classmates at Millsberry Academy describe him as very athletic, and more often than not he can be found in the Millsberry Gym during recess shooting hoops with his friends.  In fact, Thoedog's ability to knock down long-distance shots has even earned him a gold trophy at Sink the Three!<br><br>When he's not playing sports, Thoedog loves putting his mind to work on solving the most brain-stumping puzzles he can find.  He has already won several awards for this, including a gold trophy for mastering Solver.  However, when he's not busy trying to unlock the secret of a tricky puzzle, Thoedog is usually putting together some tricks of his own!  You see, he often performs magic tricks for his friends, and thanks to many hours of practice, he's become quite a skilled magician.<br><br>On weekends, Thoedog sometimes likes to put together a trip to an amusement park, which is one of his favorite things to do for fun.  If he's in the mood to take it easy, though, he can sometimes be found in his room, relaxing and listening to a variety of oldies, heavy metal, and industrial music.<br><br>In addition to his many talents, Thoedog is also a dedicated citizen of Millsberry.  He's been quite active in the effort to help keep Peabody Park clean, and recently donated a sizeable amount to the Community Center Building Fund, for which all of Millsberry is certainly grateful!<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Thoedog, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
